slations, and detailed notes on the commentaries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDiscours grecsxHistoire et critiquexThéorie, etc. 0aOratory, Ancient. 0aSpeeches, addresses, etc., GreekxHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 0aÉloquence antique. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aancient greece.  aancient world.  aantiquity.  aargumentation.  aassembly.  aathens.  aclassical rhetoric.  aclassicism.  acontemporary audience.  ademosthenes.  adidymus.  afifth century.  afuneral oration.  agreece.  agreek texts.  aharpocration.  ahellenism.  ahistorical context.  aideal audience.  alaw.  alegal.  alinguistics.  alove.  anonfiction.  aoratory.  apersia.  aphilosophy.  apolitical philosophy.  apolitical science.  apolitician.  apolitics.  apublic speaking.  arhetcomp.  arhetoric.  aspartans.  aspeeches.  astatesman.  atrials.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092730840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520927308423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520927308/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles